      "query": "How do I evaluate a fused dataframe against a gold standard test set using PyDI DataFusionEvaluator? What does DataFusionStrategy.add_evaluation_function expect and what match functions are available?",
      "response": "class\nPyDI.fusion.\nDataFusionEvaluator\n(\nstrategy\n,\n*\n,\ndebug\n=\nFalse\n,\ndebug_file\n=\nNone\n,\ndebug_format\n=\n'json'\n,\nfusion_debug_logs\n=\nNone\n)\n[source]\n\nBases:\nobject\nEvaluator for data fusion results against validation/test datasets.\nParameters\n:\nstrategy\n(\nDataFusionStrategy\n) – The fusion strategy containing evaluation rules.\ndebug\n(\nbool\n)\ndebug_file\n(\nOptional\n[\nUnion\n[\nstr\n,\nPath\n]\n]\n)\ndebug_format\n(\nstr\n)\nfusion_debug_logs\n(\nOptional\n[\nUnion\n[\nPath\n,\nstr\n,\nIterable\n[\nUnion\n[\nPath\n,\nstr\n]\n]\n]\n]\n)\nevaluate\n(\nfused_df\n,\nfused_id_column\n,\nexpected_df\n=\nNone\n,\nexpected_id_column\n=\nNone\n,\ngold_df\n=\nNone\n,\ngold_id_column\n=\nNone\n)\n[source]\n\nEvaluate fused results against an expected/validation dataset.\nParameters\n:\nfused_df\n(\npd.DataFrame\n) – The fused dataset to evaluate.\nfused_id_column\n(\nstr\n) – ID column name in the fused dataset.\nexpected_df\n(\npd.DataFrame\n,\noptional\n) – The expected/validation/test dataset.\nexpected_id_column\n(\nstr\n,\noptional\n) – ID column name in the expected dataset.\ngold_df\n(\npd.DataFrame\n,\noptional\n) – Deprecated alias for expected_df.\ngold_id_column\n(\nstr\n,\noptional\n) – Deprecated alias for expected_id_column.\nReturns\n:\n\n-----\n\ngold_df\n(\npd.DataFrame\n,\noptional\n) – Deprecated alias for expected_df.\ngold_id_column\n(\nstr\n,\noptional\n) – Deprecated alias for expected_id_column.\nReturns\n:\nDictionary of evaluation metrics.\nReturn type\n:\nDict[str, float]\nset_fusion_debug_logs\n(\nlogs\n)\n[source]\n\nLoad fusion debug log files to recover conflict inputs for evaluation.\nParameters\n:\nlogs\n(\nPath\n|\nstr\n|\nIterable\n[\nPath\n|\nstr\n]\n|\nNone\n)\nReturn type\n:\nNone\nclass\nPyDI.fusion.\nDataFusionStrategy\n(\nname\n=\n'default'\n)\n[source]\n\nBases:\nobject\nStrategy for data fusion that manages attribute fusers and evaluation rules.\nA strategy defines how to fuse each attribute by registering AttributeValueFuser\ninstances and optional evaluation rules for quality assessment.\nParameters\n:\nname\n(\nstr\n)\nadd_attribute_fuser\n(\nattribute\n,\nfuser_or_resolver\n,\nevaluation_function\n=\nNone\n,\n**\nfuser_kwargs\n)\n[source]\n\nRegister how to fuse an attribute (unified API).\nAccepts either a pre-built AttributeValueFuser (advanced usage) or a\nresolver function (simple usage). When a resolver function is provided,\nit is wrapped into an AttributeValueFuser with any extra keyword args\nsupplied via\nfuser_kwargs\n(e.g., accessor=…, required=True).\nParameters\n:\n\n-----\n\n(‘score’ or ‘similarity’). When a sequence is provided, all DataFrames\nare validated and concatenated before processing. This is compatible\nwith PyDI’s CorrespondenceSet format.\nid_column\n(\nOptional\n[\nUnion\n[\nstr\n,\nDict\n[\nstr\n,\nstr\n]\n]\n]\n) – Identifier column name(s). If a string, the same column is used for\nall datasets. If a dict, it should map dataset name -> ID column for\nthat dataset.\npre_normalized\n(\nbool\n,\ndefault False\n) – When True, assume\ndatasets\nalready contain string\n_id\ncolumns and\ncorrespondences\nalready use string identifiers. Use this when inputs\nwere normalized upstream to avoid redundant copies.\nReturns\n:\nList of record groups representing connected components.\nReturn type\n:\nList[\nRecordGroup\n]\nPyDI.fusion.evaluation module\n\nEvaluation framework for data fusion in PyDI.\nThis module provides tools for evaluating the quality of fusion results\nagainst validation/test datasets.\nclass\nPyDI.fusion.evaluation.\nDataFusionEvaluator\n(\nstrategy\n,\n*\n,\ndebug\n=\nFalse\n,\ndebug_file\n=\nNone\n,\ndebug_format\n=\n'json'\n,\nfusion_debug_logs\n=\nNone\n)\n[source]\n\nBases:\nobject\nEvaluator for data fusion results against validation/test datasets.\nParameters\n:\nstrategy\n(\nDataFusionStrategy\n\n-----\n\ngold_id_column\n(\nstr\n,\noptional\n) – Deprecated alias for expected_id_column.\nReturns\n:\nDictionary of evaluation metrics.\nReturn type\n:\nDict[str, float]\nset_fusion_debug_logs\n(\nlogs\n)\n[source]\n\nLoad fusion debug log files to recover conflict inputs for evaluation.\nParameters\n:\nlogs\n(\nPath\n|\nstr\n|\nIterable\n[\nPath\n|\nstr\n]\n|\nNone\n)\nReturn type\n:\nNone\nPyDI.fusion.evaluation.\nboolean_match\n(\nfused_value\n,\nexpected_value\n)\n[source]\n\nEvaluation function for boolean values with flexible interpretation.\nHandles various boolean representations:\n- True/False, true/false, yes/no, 1/0, “true”/”false”, etc.\nReturn type\n:\nbool\nPyDI.fusion.evaluation.\ncalculate_consistency_metrics\n(\nfused_df\n)\n[source]\n\nCalculate consistency metrics for a fused dataset.\nParameters\n:\nfused_df\n(\npd.DataFrame\n) – The fused dataset with fusion metadata.\nReturns\n:\nDictionary of consistency metrics.\nReturn type\n:\nDict[str, float]\nPyDI.fusion.evaluation.\ncalculate_coverage_metrics\n(\ndatasets\n,\nfused_df\n)\n[source]\n\nCalculate coverage metrics comparing input to output.\nParameters\n:\ndatasets\n(\nList\n[\npd.DataFrame\n]\n) – Original input datasets.\nfused_df\n(\npd.DataFrame\n) – The fused result dataset.\nReturns\n:"
